<div class="content"> <div class="container-fluid"> <div class="row"> <div class="col-md-12"> <div class="card"> <div class="content p-b-30"> <h4 class="w-100 label-warning p-t-15 p-b-15 p-l-30 f-400">FAQ</h4> <div id="simple-accordion-alt-2" class="accordion accordion-alt"> <h3 class="accordion-header">How do I get started?</h3> <div class="accordion-content" data-wrapper="true" style="height: 0px; position: relative; overflow: hidden;" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false"> <div> <p>Our system uses automatic functions, so there is no need to provide personally information during registration. Just enter some basic information in the appropriate field and click “register”. This will take you straight to your personal control panel dashboard.</p> </div> </div> <h3 class="accordion-header">What payment processors do you accept?</h3> <div class="accordion-content" data-wrapper="true" style="overflow:hidden;height:0;position:relative;" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false"> <div> <p>Only accept Bitcoin (BTC).</p> </div> </div> <h3 class="accordion-header">What is the minimum investment amount?</h3> <div class="accordion-content" data-wrapper="true" style="overflow:hidden;height:0;position:relative;" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false"> <div> <p>The minimum amount allowed for deposit is: 50 USD</p> </div> </div> <h3 class="accordion-header">Can I have more than one account?</h3> <div class="accordion-content" data-wrapper="true" style="overflow:hidden;height:0;position:relative;" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false"> <div> <p>We don’t allow users to have multiple accounts. Accounts are restricted to one per computer and one per member. Not following the COINREUM rules about this issue and others can result in serious consequences. Having multiple accounts per person or computer can lead to accounts being closed and deactivated. Deposits are returned in the event of account closure, but not any winnings.</p> </div> </div> <h3 class="accordion-header">I forgot my password! Can I recover it?</h3> <div class="accordion-content" data-wrapper="true" style="overflow:hidden;height:0;position:relative;" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false"> <div> <p>Of course you can recover your lost password. There is a password recovery form offered for this very occasion.</p> </div> </div> <h3 class="accordion-header">What about a forgotten email address? Can that be recovered?</h3> <div class="accordion-content" data-wrapper="true" style="overflow:hidden;height:0;position:relative;" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false"> <div> <p>If you forget the email address you used to sign up then please contact customer support. Your email account can be recovered, but you will need to provide some basic information to verify your identity. This is an important step to maintain security for our members.</p> </div> </div> <h3 class="accordion-header">Can I have more than one active deposit?</h3> <div class="accordion-content" data-wrapper="true" style="overflow:hidden;height:0;position:relative;" role="tabpanel" aria-expanded="false"> <div> <p>Yes, all deposits are handled individually and you can have as many deposits as you wish.</p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div>